Why is are the children of the `PageHome_Section` not rendered

The issue you're facing with the `PageHome_Section` not rendering its children lies in how you are calling and using the `@PageHome_Section` template. The problem is that within the `@PageHome_Section` template, you have a `<details>` element, but you do not actually render any content inside it. This means that the `children...` placeholder where the actual content should be rendered remains empty.

In the `@PageHome_SectionDevices` and `@PageHome_SectionGroups` templates, you are making an AJAX call (`hx-get`) to fetch data, but you are not rendering any content based on this data. The `<span>` elements are used to trigger the AJAX request, but they do not display the fetched data or render additional HTML.

To fix this issue, you need to ensure that the `children...` placeholder is used correctly within the `@PageHome_Section` template and that the `hx-get` attribute updates the content of the `<details>` element dynamically. Here’s how you can adjust your code:

1. **Render Content Dynamically**: When using `hx-get`, ensure that the target (specified by `hx-target`) has a structure to accept new content.
2. **Update the Target Element**: Modify the structure of the `PageHome_Section` template so that it updates dynamically based on the AJAX response.

Here’s an updated version of your templates with these considerations:

```templ picow-led/components/page-home.templ
package components

templ PageHome() {
	@Layout(
		LayoutOptions{
			PageTitle:      "PicoW LED",
			AdditionalHead: PageHome_AdditionalHead(),
		},
	) {
		{{ id := "section-devices" }}
		@PageHome_Section(id) {
			<summary>Devices</summary>
			<span
				hx-get={ props.Get }
				hx-trigger="load, reload from:body"
				hx-target="#section-devices .content"
			></span>
		}
		{{ id = "section-groups" }}
		@PageHome_Section(id) {
			<summary>Groups</summary>
			<span
				hx-get={ props.Get }
				hx-trigger="load, reload from:body"
				hx-target="#section-groups .content"
			></span>
		}
	}
}

templ PageHome_AdditionalHead() {
}

templ PageHome_Section(id string) {
	<details id={ id }>
		<summary>{ content... }</summary>
		<div class="content"></div>
	</details>
}
```

In this updated version:
- The `PageHome_Section` template now includes a `<div>` with the class `.content` inside the `<details>` element. This div is used to display dynamically loaded content.
- The AJAX trigger in both `@PageHome_SectionDevices` and `@PageHome_SectionGroups` specifies that the fetched data should be targeted at this `.content` div.

This setup ensures that the `children...` placeholder within `@PageHome_Section` is used correctly to render dynamic content based on the AJAX response.
